    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-cpb-accepted-2026q1",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/cardiac-devices-vv-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 requirements. CFD hemolysis predictions demonstrate RH < 1 at all 5 CPB operating points with mean absolute error of 4.2% against experimental reference data. The experimental validation dataset predates the January 2026 model revision by approximately three months; the assessment team reviewed the scope of the revision (boundary-layer mesh refinement and turbulence-model coefficient adjustment) and concluded residual impact on RH predictions is low for the current submission. Full re-validation is planned for Q2 2026 prior to design freeze. Credibility sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission at Medium assurance level.",
